added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: The Island
added.description: While trying to sail to Japan, the Baby Bears get stranded on an island. Luckily, they meet Dave and Karla, who help with survival on the island while looking for an escape.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Cupcake Job
added.description: When the Bears' beloved laptop breaks, they finally have the need to do something they've never done before: get jobs. Working at a trendy cupcake shop, the Bears find  that the working world is much tougher than they realized.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: Point to the Plaza
added.description: When a Gloop infestation takes over the plaza, Point arrives to contain the situation.

added.title: Crossover Nexus
added.description: When KO finds himself trapped inside an mysterious place, he encounters other Cartoon Network Heroes and they band together to escape.

added.title: Monster Party
added.description: Enid is faced with a choice when her old friends from Ghoul School show up.

added.title: Final Exams
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up with an unlikely ally to take on an unlikely foe.

added.title: CarolQuest
added.description: Carol is forced to bring KO along as she defends the Plaza from a new threat.

added.title: You're Everybody's Sidekick
added.description: KO sets out to prove to Enid that being helpful is rewarding by helping people all around the Lakewood Plaza Turbo.

added.title: You're Level 100!
added.description: When KO finally gets a Pow Card, he finds out he's level 100, instantly making him a celebrity and the idol of everyone.

added.title: I Am Dendy
added.description: KO helps a strange girl from school, Dendy, get the parts she needs to repair her high tech backpack.

added.title: You Are Rad
added.description: When KO forgets his name tag, Rad lets him use his, which results in everyone thinking KO is Rad, including Rad himself.

added.title: Nemesis
added.description: A shadowy figure named Peace Master targets the Candy Kingdom elite.

added.title: Dentist
added.description: Finn's aching tooth leaves him with no other option but to go to the dentist.

added.title: Friends Forever
added.description: Ice King plots to form a perfect circle of confidants.

added.title: Hoots
added.description: A charismatic stranger in Finn's dream leads Cosmic Owl to shirk his duties.

added.title: A Glitch Is a Glitch
added.description: Ice King creates a computer virus to delete everybody except him and Princess Bubblegum.

added.title: Puhoy
added.description: Stuck inside the treehouse during a sword storm, Jake builds a pillow fort while Finn goes to a different world.

added.title: James Baxter the Horse
added.description: Finn and Jake meet a horse with the power to make sad people happy.

added.title: In Your Footsteps
added.description: A bear befriends Finn and Jake, but what are his true intentions?

added.title: Card Wars
added.description: Finn & Jake embark on an epic game of Card Quest.

added.title: Lady & Peebles
added.description: PB and Lady Rainicorn go on a quest to find Finn & Jake who are missing after fighting the Ice King.

added.title: Blood Under the Skin
added.description: Finn goes on an embarrassing quest to get armor to fit in with some really cool knights.

added.title: Mystery Train
added.description: Finn and Jake get wrapped up in a high speed whodunit!

added.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
added.description: Finn becomes jealous of Princes Bubblegum's new suitor.

added.title: Ocean of Fear
added.description: Finn faces his biggest challenge yet...overcoming his fear of water.

added.title: Gut Grinder
added.description: Finn and Jake chase a mysterious villain who's been stealing gold from helpless villages.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo! Pirates Ahoy
removed.description: It's horror on the high seas when Scooby-Doo and the gang take a creepy cruise into one of the world's most mysterious places, the legendary Bermuda Triangle! If Scooby-Doo, Shaggy and the gang can't solve this mystery, they may have to walk the plank.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo! Camp Scare
removed.description: Welcome to Camp Little Moose where the counselors are friendly, the activities are endless and the urban legends are intense. In fact, every time someone tells a ghost story, the creepy creature comes to life!

removed.title: Scooby-Doo and the Loch Ness Monster
removed.description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. travel to Scotland to visit Daphne's relatives at Blake Castle, which is situated on Loch Ness, home of the legendary creature who has recently been stalking Daphne's cousin Fiona.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo! The Mystery Begins
removed.description: What brings best friends together? For Daphne, Velma, Fred, Shaggy and Shaggy's spunky pup, Scooby-Doo, it's a mystery! The Mystery Begins takes fans back to when four teenage sleuths first met.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo! Abracadabra-Doo
removed.description: When a secluded school for magicians faces danger from a fantastical flying creature outside and sinister forces inside, there's just one thing to say: Scooby-Doo! Abracadabra-Doo.

removed.description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery, Inc. gang are in for a creepy encounter with a monster from Mexico in the mucho spooky, all-new Scooby-Doo movie. The sleuths take a well-earned vacation to visit a friend in Mexico and celebrate the Day of the Dead.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo and the Cyber Chase

removed.title: Scooby-Doo and the Gourmet Ghost

removed.description: When Shaggy develops a hysterical response to fear, his doctor suggests that he stay away from any Mystery Inc. adventures. At Daphne's suggestion, Scooby-Doo and the gang head to a resort spa in a desert town for a relaxing vacation.

removed.description: Mystery, Inc. heads to Blowout Beach for a real swinging beach party. But when the Ghost Pirates threaten to harsh the good vibes, it's up to the Scooby and the gang to get the party back on track and save the day!

removed.title: Scooby-Doo! and the Goblin King
removed.description: To face a Goblin King, courage is crucial. So for Scooby-Doo and Shaggy, the odds are against them!

removed.title: Scooby-Doo in Where's My Mummy?
removed.description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. gang become involved in a supernatural mystery in Egypt.

removed.title: The Road
removed.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

removed.title: Everyday Bears
removed.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

removed.title: Grizzly the Movie
removed.description: Grizz gets cast in a movie about a Grizzly Bear! But Grizz soon realizes the movie's depiction of grizzly bears is not what he had in mind.

removed.title: Yuri and the Bear

removed.title: Captain Craboo
removed.description: The Bears are reunited with their pet crab, Captain Craboo. But after an unfortunate run-in with Nom Nom, the Bears may lose their pet forever.

removed.title: Shush Ninjas

removed.title: My Fair Carol
removed.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

removed.title: Jethro's All Yours
removed.description: KO gets his first solo mission!

removed.title: Plaza Film Festival
removed.description: When the plaza has its own film festival, KO, Enid and Rad are sure their entry will win!

removed.title: Presenting Joe Cuppa
removed.description: KO tries to help his favorite comedian, Joe Cuppa.

removed.title: Glory Days
removed.description: KO does a school report on Carol.

removed.title: Seasons Change
removed.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

removed.title: Your World Is an Illusion
removed.description: KO tries to help a hero in need and ends up needing some help of his own.

removed.title: My Two Favorite People
removed.description: Jake tries to broker peace between Rainicorn and Finn.

removed.description: Finn must keep his promise to Princess Bubblegum and cover up the zombie problem they've created.

removed.description: Finn must help plan the Ice King's bachelor party.

removed.title: The Ultimate Adventure: Come Along with Me
removed.description: The fate of Ooo is revealed to two adventurers in the distant future. Princess Bubblegum gathers her allies while Finn searches for a way to prevent the coming Great Gum War.
